hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: What do you study? pro agra uk What's clear right now is that equal access to Social Security benefits will most swiftly be extended to couples who live in the 14 jurisdictions where same-sex marriage already is legal: California, Connecticut, Delaware, the District of Columbia, Iowa, Maine, Maryland, Massachusetts, Minnesota (takes effect Aug. 1), New Hampshire, New York, Rhode Island (takes effect Aug. 1), Vermont and Washington. Also, because District of Columbia laws are applicable to citizens living overseas, same-sex U.S. couples living outside the country should be able to claim Social Security benefits.
